        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-10-26 19:58:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nIn the IB test, it looks like the ZFS inodes are consuming 32KB per inode. That is quite a bit more than I expected. It is using this much space for the 191 inodes that exist at the start of the test also, so it makes me wonder if there is some config difference (e.g. number of OSTs or maybe the default stripe could) since I don't think that the IB vs. TCP network should make any difference here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
